Class FedmIsoTableItem

java.lang.Object
  de.feig.FedmIsoTableItem
All Implemented Interfaces:
Fedm, FedmIscReaderConst, FedmTableItem
public class FedmIsoTableItem
extends java.lang.Object
implements FedmTableItem, FedmIscReaderConst, Fedm

Table class for the OBID i-scan® and OBID® classic-pro reader family.
This table collects all data and bean methods, when the reader works in the ISO-Host Mode.

Method Detail

isDataValid

public boolean isDataValid(java.lang.String dataID)
Query method for validity of table data.

Specified by:
isDataValid in interface FedmTableItem
Parameters:
dataID - String to identify one data member
Returns:
true, if data member valid

Description:
Overloaded method to query the validity of one table data member.
With each query, one table data member can be checked if it is read from the transponder. The validity flag is never set with the setData methods of this class.
The transferred dataID contains a string for data identification.
The following strings can be used:
  • "DATA_SNR"
  • "DATA_TRTYPE"
  • "DATA_EPC"
  • "DATA_EPC_TYPE"
  • "DATA_DSFID"
  • "DATA_TRINFO"
  • "DATA_OPTINFO"
  • "DATA_AFI"
  • "DATA_IC_REF"
  • "DATA_IS_SELECTED"
  • "DATA_BLOCK_SIZE"
  • "DATA_IS_BLOCK_SIZE_SET"
  • "DATA_MEM_SIZE"
  • "DATA_IS_ISO14443_4_INFO"
If dataID is not one of the constants, listed above, the method returns false.

verifyDataBlocks

public int verifyDataBlocks(int blockNr,
                            int blockCnt)
Method for verify received with sent transponder data block(s).

Specified by:
verifyDataBlocks in interface FedmTableItem
Parameters:
blockNr - first number of data block
blockCnt - number of blocks to be verified
Returns:
Fedm.OK or an error code (<0)

Description:
This table has separate memories for received and transmit data. This allows the verification of sent with received transponder data.
This method verifies only complete data blocks.
The table attribute blockSize, which contains the number of bytes in each data block, is used internally. Thus, the blockSize attribute must be previously set.
One way to set the blockSize attribute is to read a data block from the transponder. The receive protocol contains the blockSize and the attribute is set automatically. Another way is to query the System Information from the transponder, if the transponder supports this request.
If the content of the data blocks are equal, then the method returns Fedm.OK, otherwise Fedm.ERROR_VERIFY.
If an error occurs, method returns an error code (<0).

verifyDataBytes

public int verifyDataBytes(int startByte,
                           int byteCnt)
Method for verify received with sent transponder data byte(s).

Specified by:
verifyDataBytes in interface FedmTableItem
Parameters:
startByte - first byte
byteCnt - number of bytes to be verified
Returns:
Fedm.OK or an error code (<0)

Description:
This table has separate memories for received and transmit data. This allows the verification of sent with received transponder data. This method verifies data bytes without the limitation of the blocksize.
If the content of the data bytes are equal, then the method returns Fedm.OK, otherwise Fedm.ERROR_VERIFY.
If an error occurs, the lastError attribute is set and the method returns an error code (<0).
